    },
    "body": "I'm currently using ROCM with RDNA3. I've been trying to use compressed-tensors for a while, and I thought it was only supported on CUDA.\n\nThis change simply avoids entering: CompressedTensorsWNA16MarlinMoEMethod for CUDA when using ROCM and allows inference of a model like the following:\n\n[jart25/Qwen3-VL-30B-A3B-Instruct-AWQ-8bit\n](https://huggingface.co/jart25/Qwen3-VL-30B-A3B-Instruct-AWQ-8bit)\nusing: CompressedTensorsWNA16MoEMethod and ExllamaLinearKernel\n\nNote that it must be run with:\n\nexport VLLM_USE_TRITON_AWQ=1",
    "created_at": "2025-10-20T07:50:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-15T17:04:06Z",
    "closed_at": "2025-10-21T14:43:23Z",
    "merged_at": "2025-10-21T14:43:23Z",
